article.description: — Abdoulaye scored 22 points as High Point beat Illinois State 74-72 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Thiam scores 22 as High Point takes down Illinois State 74-72
article.linkText: Thiam scores 22 as High Point takes down Illinois State 74-72
article.story: ESTERO, Fla. -- — Abdoulaye scored 22 points as High Point beat Illinois State 74-72 on Tuesday night. Thiam shot 7 for 14 (4 for 7 from 3-point range) and 4 of 5 from the free-throw line for the Panthers (3-2). Trae Benham added 12 points while going 4 of 8 (3 for 7 from 3-point range), and they also had 10 rebounds. Duke Miles had 11 points and shot 5 for 8, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc. The Redbirds (3-2) were led in scoring by Darius Burford, who finished with 17 points. Johnny Kinziger added 14 points for Illinois State. In addition, Malachi Poindexter finished with 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
